strategy_rules: Avoid tokens with volume spikes greater than 3× (e.g., 3.28×, 3.96×) because all such cases in the data were losing trades; moderate spikes ≤2.5× are acceptable.
Require age between 6-24h - trades in this age range had the highest win rate (46.2%) among all age categories.
Target buy‑ratio > 1.0. Ratios below 0.9 (e.g., 0.5, 0.9) appear only in losing trades, while ratios between 1.0‑3.5 capture 7 of 8 winning trades.

Prioritize tokens showing a *pressure_heavy_buying* pattern rather than merely normal volume, because this category delivers an average ROI of **+527.9 %** and a win rate of **37.5 %** (8 trades), outperforming the vol_normal group (+504 % ROI, 33.3 % win).

Target buy‑ratio values **1.0‑3.5** for the bulk of trades (captures 7 of 8 winners). Ratios **>4** can generate extreme upside (e.g., ratio 6.84 → +4343.9 % ROI) but are rare and high‑risk; limit exposure to such outliers to ≤10 % of allocated capital.
Do not trade tokens older than 24 h; the 24h+ age group (3 trades) shows 0 % win rate and an average ROI of –9.7 %.
Consider age 1‑6 h for high upside; this segment (4 trades) yields an average ROI of +1198.5 % despite a lower win rate (25 %).
Avoid tokens with volume spikes **>3×**; the only two trades with spikes of 3.28× and 3.96× were losses, giving an average ROI of **‑56.5 %** (0 wins / 2 trades).

When chasing very high upside, allocate a small portion of capital to **age 1‑6 h** tokens, which produced an average ROI of **+1198.5 %** (4 trades) despite a 25 % win rate; combine this with the more consistent **6‑24 h** window (avg ROI +181.3 %, win rate 31.8 %) for balanced performance.
